Otter</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usubbiano.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Subbiano</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>n00b!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/27/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>3:02:09 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: LOH - now an uber taunt</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Some points-<br>
<br>
LoH agroes as a heal, no more no less. If you use it early then the mob classifies you as a healer and also a melee'er, hence the high agro. If you use it ealry before clerics start CHealing, then you will have both main healer agro and a melee's agro.<br>
<br>
Taunt doesn't work on mobs that DT unless you are 60, or are a higher level than said mob. Case closed next topic.<br>
<br>
DA has an inate ability that automatically drops you to the bottom of the mob's hate list. It's part of the spell. Anyone who says they hold agro during a DA is full of shit, unless they are the ONLY PC who has the mob agroed. Taunt does work while DA but you are working from a zero hate base, so any character that has healed/nuked/ or hit the mob is way ahead of you.<br>
<br>
In conclusion the only time you should DA during a major mob encounter is if the main taunter loses agro to you (not likely the way pallies do damage if we don't stun or taunt). The DA will drop you on the hate list, probably shifting to the main taunter.<br>
<br>
Take it or leave it, there's my points. I know hate list more than most because of my AoE experience. AoE pulling requires a fairly in-depth knowledge of agro and hate list (if it's done right).<br>
<br>
